SEA CHECK

sea_check confirms that the substrate's seas can be created and addressed correctly
after bond_check passes, sea_check tries to allocate small test seas in each device target (cpu and gpu) and writes a known pattern into them, then reads it back
if any sea cannot be allocated or the readback does not match, the substrate is broken and boot aborts
without working seas there is no place for any citizen to live

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe bios.rana
observe bond_check.rana

the 7 properties of sea_check:
1 ENERGY one point five: high, this is critical infrastructure verification
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1
5 COHERENCE one: readback must match exactly
6 COUPLING zero at idle, one when running
7 OBSERVER one

VERB run
allocate a small test sea on the cpu device, write a pattern, read it back, compare
allocate a small test sea on the gpu device, write a pattern, read it back, compare
free both test seas after verification
if all four steps succeed, emit pass; if any step fails, emit fail

VERB pass
emit a positive signal that allows chemistry_check to proceed

VERB fail
emit silence and halt boot
the body cannot exist without functioning substrate
this is non-negotiable

a sea check is not a hardware test
the GPU might be perfectly healthy but if the substrate cannot route bodies to it, the body cannot live there
sea_check verifies the bridge between substrate and silicon, not silicon itself
